Notice setUp() and tearDown() run once per test method, not once for the whole class 
— that's what keeps tests independent of each other.

Step 5: Why This Matters

Without @Before/@After                        With @Before/@After

You create new BankAccount                      Created once in setUp(), reused by all tests
(100.0) inside every test method     --         reused by all tests

Risk of tests accidentally           --         Each test gets a guaranteed fresh object
sharing/mutating state

Code duplication                     --         DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) test code

Harder to update fixture             --         Change fixture in one place
(change in many places)
